PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FThe head of Britain's biggest police
OL,8,Fforce has thrown down the gauntlet to
OL,9,Fthe phone industry to take action over
OL,10,Fstolen devices by June 1 or face being
OL,11,Fforced to do so by law.
OL,13,FPhone companies are leaving customers
OL,14,Fat risk until they take action to make
OL,15,Fstolen devices "unusable bricks",
OL,16,FMetropolitan Police Commissioner Sir
OL,17,FMark Rowley said.
OL,26,@wD@POUwD@`O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FThe Met has some of the highest rates
OL,8,Fper thousand people of personal
OL,9,Frobbery and theft from the person in
OL,10,FEngland and Wales, among which phones
OL,11,Fare a "significant" problem.
OL,13,FSir Mark told delegates at the
OL,14,FInternational Mobile Phone Crime
OL,15,FConference in central London that he
OL,16,Fdoes not understand why the telecoms
OL,17,Fgiants have not done more.
OL,26,@sD@GOUsD@SO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FHe said that the Met will call on the
OL,8,FHome Secretary to change laws to force
OL,9,Fphone companies to take action if
OL,10,Fnecessary, and will encourage
OL,11,Finternational law enforcement to do
OL,12,Fthe same.
OL,14,F"I'm setting a clear public marker, if
OL,15,Fby the first of June, industry has not
OL,16,Fcome to the table in a genuinely
OL,17,Fserious and solution-focused way, with
OL,18,Fconcrete commitments on stolen mobile
OL,19,Fphones... the Met will formally write
OL,20,Fto the Home Secretary to ask that she
OL,21,Flegislates."
OL,26,@vD@AOU}D@LO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FThe force wants to make resetting
OL,8,Fphones more difficult, with
OL,9,Frequirements for multi-factor
OL,10,Fauthentication and time delays; moves
OL,11,Fto stop parts being sold without
OL,12,Fdevice matching serial numbers, and
OL,13,Fthe ability to block devices globally
OL,14,Fin real time.
OL,16,FHe added: "We will set out that for
OL,17,Fnearly three years we have sought
OL,18,Fmeaningful engagement with phone
OL,19,Fmanufacturers and their response to
OL,20,Fdate does not match the scale of harm
OL,21,Fand risk to their customers."
OL,26,@xD@KOU}D@]O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FMayor of London Sadiq Khan said there
OL,8,Fis "no reason" why in a year's time
OL,9,Fthere should not be fully accessible
OL,10,Fserial numbers for officials and "kill
OL,11,Fswitches" for stolen phones.
OL,13,FThe international trade in stolen
OL,14,Fphones is worth millions of dollars,
OL,15,Fwith a device stolen in London worth
OL,16,Fmore in countries like China because
OL,17,Fit has none of the government
OL,18,Frestrictions put in place by
OL,19,Fauthorities there.
OL,26,@pD@DOUpD@NO]rD@bOUsD@IO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FIn the UK, the Met has seen adverts on
OL,8,FSnapchat offering children as much as
OL,9,F#380 to steal a single iPhone, with a
OL,10,Fbonus of #100 for stealing 10.
OL,12,FSir Mark said: "The exploitation of
OL,13,Fchildren in this trade is not just
OL,14,Fabout individual offences.
OL,16,F"It's an entry point into organised
OL,17,Fcrime.
OL,26,@tD@POUxD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,F"Children recruited to snatch phones
OL,8,Ffor quick cash are being groomed into
OL,9,Fcriminal networks, normalised into
OL,10,Foffending behaviour and pushed further
OL,11,Finto exploitation.
OL,13,F"What begins as one device on a street
OL,14,Fcorner becomes a pathway into debt,
OL,15,Fcoercion, violence and deeper
OL,16,Fcriminality."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUxD@MO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FThe Met wants anti-theft protection
OL,8,Fswitched on by default, stolen phones
OL,9,Fto be rendered unusable, and better
OL,10,Faccess to IMEI (International Mobile
OL,11,FEquipment Identity) data to make it
OL,12,Feasier to return devices to their
OL,13,Fowners.
OL,15,FFigures released under Freedom of
OL,16,FInformation legislation show only a
OL,17,Ffraction of devices taken in London
OL,18,Fare returned to their owners.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FBetween 2017 and February 27 2024, a
OL,8,Ftotal 587,498 phones were stolen in
OL,9,FLondon excluding the City, 13,998 of
OL,10,Fwhich were recovered, and 573,500 were
OL,11,Fnot.
OL,13,FDelegates from countries including
OL,14,FJapan, Brazil, Spain, and the United
OL,15,FStates attended the conference, the
OL,16,Ffirst of its kind.
OL,18,FSir Mark said weak security means
OL,19,Fcriminals can still bypass locks,
OL,20,Falter IMEIs, and sell parts that are
OL,21,Fnot cryptographically tied to devices.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FHe said there would be no criminal
OL,8,Fmarket if a stolen phone were
OL,9,Funusable, and called for similar
OL,10,Faction to that taken by the car
OL,11,Findustry to make car radios less
OL,12,Fattractive to steal.
OL,14,F"Phone manufacturing software
OL,15,Fcompanies have invested massively in
OL,16,Fpreventing access to your data.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,F"It's an escalating war with
OL,8,Ffraudsters and cyber criminals, but
OL,9,Fthey've been successful enough to
OL,10,Fallow us to run our lives, including
OL,11,Four finances, on our phones.
OL,13,F"Whilst they've worked hard on the
OL,14,Ffinancial and data security of our
OL,15,Fphones, they spend far less attention
OL,16,Fon the physical safety of their
OL,17,Fcustomers who walk through cities with
OL,18,Fa #1,000 or #2,000 device held loosely
OL,19,Fin their hands.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,F"If a stolen phone were to become an
OL,8,Funusable brick and the parts were not
OL,9,Frecyclable, there would be no criminal
OL,10,Fmarket."
OL,12,FHe added: "I do not understand why
OL,13,Ftech companies leave their clients at
OL,14,Frisk despite two or three years of
OL,15,Fdiscussions.
OL,17,F"Until this device is worthless, the
OL,18,Fmarket will remain attractive to
OL,19,Forganised crime."
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@HO]tD@KOUyD@AOU{D@QO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G12/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FLast month the Met said that the
OL,8,Fnumber of recorded phone thefts in
OL,9,FLondon went from 81,365 in 2024 to
OL,10,F71,391 last year.
OL,12,FSeparate figures available on the
OL,13,FMet's crime data website show that in
OL,14,F2023 there were 52,820 thefts from the
OL,15,Fperson where a phone was taken, and
OL,16,F14,326 robberies; the figures for 2024
OL,17,Fwere 70,249 thefts and 11,125
OL,18,Frobberies; and for 2025 61,292 thefts
OL,19,Fand 10,207 robberies.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G13/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40314
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FIn the space of the month to mid-
OL,8,FFebruary, the Met arrested 248 people
OL,9,Fover phone theft and recovered around
OL,10,F770 stolen handsets.
OL,12,FThe force is using high-powered e-
OL,13,Fbikes and drones as part of its
OL,14,Foperations to stop phone theft.
OL,16,FBut in a report for the London
OL,17,FPolicing Board, Sir Mark warned the
OL,18,FMet remains "an outlier" for the
OL,19,Fnumber of personal robberies per
OL,20,Fthousand people, and theft from the
OL,21,Fperson.
OL,26,@zD@MOUzD@XO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G14/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40315
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773331876
OL,3,CMet tells phone companies to produce
OL,4,C'unusable bricks' in bid to tackle
OL,5,Ctheft
OL,7,FThe force also solves one of the
OL,8,Fsmallest proportion of these offences
OL,9,Fcompared with others in England and
OL,10,FWales.
OL,12,FIn the year to the end of December
OL,13,F2025, 6.9% of personal robbery cases
OL,14,Fended with a suspect being identified
OL,15,Fand dealt with, while the rate was
OL,16,F0.9% for theft from the person.
OL,18,FIn Westminster, between 69% and 72% of
OL,19,Fthefts from the person and personal
OL,20,Frobberies each week involve phones.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G15/16
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
